result.execSummary:
The defendant Barry Martin Frederick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant shall not possess any illegal substances or drug paraphernalia as defined in Chapter 961.

Defendant to pay supervision fees as determined by DOC.
Defendant shall submit to any assessments and fully participate in any counseling deemed appropriate by the Agent and abide by any treatment recommendations.
Defendant shall possess prescription medications only by valid prescription, and take in the manner and method as prescribed by a physician.
Defendant shall obtain prescriptions from only one (1) pharmacy.
Defendant shall report any changes to medical appointments or medications to his Agent within 48 hours.
